item.title: Midterm Report: Moussa Sissoko beginning to find his feet
item.description: There has been few home debuts more memorable that Moussa Sissoko’s against Chelsea in February 2013. Jonas Gutierrez had given NUFC a first half lead but two stunning goals from Frank Lampard and Juan Mata turned the tie in favour of the Blues. Then came Moussa to the rescue. A quick break from midfield set Yoan Gouffran behind the back four and he tried his luck with a strong left-footed effort that Petr Cech could only parry perfectly into the path of Sissoko to tap into an empty net.
